**SUSTAINABLE TECHNOLOGY ADOPTION SCORE: 69/100**

Technology Adoption: 17/25  
Innovation Leadership: 18/25  
Measurable Impact: 17/25  
Future Strategy: 11/15  
Industry Position: 6/10

Overview
- Microchip Technology has a clear, documented sustainability program and has deployed a mix of operational renewable-energy projects and product-side low‑power technologies. It demonstrates solid mid‑tier execution and credible measurable wins (notably in Scope 1/2 reductions and an on‑site floating solar plant), plus active R&D and partnerships (mSiC, low‑power FPGAs, sustainability reference designs). However, it currently trails the largest foundry/IDM leaders on scale of renewables procurement, SBTi‑validated targets and publicly disclosed, fully‑granular absolute emissions data. Key evidence and recent examples (2022–2025) are below. Sources from the research are listed at the end. [Microchip Sustainability Report / corporate pages and press summaries]([Microchip Sustainability Report 2023](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGilHBlI-Y57V1uFl3T_z06gy0d9dNRBtp8dnl-AjIK9NV-D4DNwI9MM0OMJGhNx60RjMm9ar4QuZeTQnVpO1oaDFSqbQbAKnL4guA_er5xnLqMFDs=); [PowerElectronicsNews coverage](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHH8SV6b3HIxQnRvLB7LlvOFzW4P05FMXmeS27vxMgVYyoglthoCDkmtn150pKUmSoLbHl9_bZyFI0k-ogLhr-IgGzyeyShIbSeTRZM5Z8aS76NjF3NsXw-vxC6MijogLZDMjE24LMY51b8Vo_qeJy6DIktE5cRGlYkm5hcKQUzwOuZTT7xRZl7V2zZf5ZXPDYGCL72H2k2gwZz4_w6ZJ-CxvOLkHdZjabh1o2PdBiIyhyAR5S3GWDs70eaA0hMMQ==)).

Findings by research area (with examples and citations)

Technology Adoption — what sustainable technologies has Microchip implemented? (17/25)
- Renewable energy: on‑site/near‑site projects and PPAs — notable example is a 3.8 MW floating solar farm at Microchip’s Thailand facility (2024) expected to supply ~16% of that facility’s annual electricity; company says it has expanded its renewable portfolio and increased renewable electricity share year‑over‑year. [PowerElectronicsNews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGEZSFZVtnFnRva5iz-mdoHVnOTPpjW5zQc1vWkhmbkI-QJswGZeYZHhODfXAtLWUJ7RNP7Y6xKr-rTNWVbEueWA0CMMZWLFIhiBRNxw5WqoTsUppT4sfmx6Nqn1M91D5Qoy5GVWPKNzzSzuVzD8Z4nKqqEnJQx3-f5SftOKi8YfA865qylV9UlvAAGFr83GX0NXRvh4IjNVTWb6pvRt6gIjNILdkGqczHeoeKMuatLtL1BbXqBtfixV-rIFSXA) [PowerElectronicsNews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHH8SV6b3HIxQnRvLB7LlvOFzW4P05FMXmeS27vxMgVYyoglthoCDkmtn150pKUmSoLbHl9_bZyFI0k-ogLhr-IgGzyeyShIbSeTRZM5Z8aS76NjF3NsXw-vxC6MijogLZDMjE24LMY51b8Vo_qeJy6DIktE5cRGlYkm5hcKQUzwOuZTT7xRZl7V2zZf5ZXPDYGCL72H2k2gwZz4_w6ZJ-CxvOLkHdZjabh1o2PdBiIyhyAR5S3GWDs70eaA0hMMQ==).
- Energy‑efficiency in products: development of low‑power architectures (edge/data center/IoT), claims that some FPGAs deliver ~2× GOPS/watt vs competitors; product reference solutions showcased for meters, microinverters, heat pumps and EV charging (Enlit Europe 2024). [Microchip product pages / event coverage](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEI0f2YkSRPbegrvKE4m2PYUIG3AD0PQzRgR2NAkUOKFsM9jEuqJSO8yo6DvdEwb5lXW8ukcO7QxW0_jkHS8aiKDa1alYLaHrve5zD2AeK-1KLCNVAzmOat1ubKYf-qsyyeHB79FflMW8VuSwBbKMsj55wx0sbkE1ZqOrBxI_uX2AuSvYrgB97hkAL4UWsrbZwJNqfvAg==) [YouTube / Enlit showcase](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGOgOL5pt2ICPRa-_7YOB8A5rNiJE8ux0CQ7YcP_Fi_ur9Y5IVpOKf8J5ekJqI4QqJ-jAxwIhiHIGNKrYrU6jMBcyAJYhkQE73tPpsdpehOUXUMp-z33K2CYiwFGgbXXVRAYaiGINg=) [PowerElectronicsNews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG5e7JbJf1GtcKK1wMk57uJ8r3Xd7fzhk5rtnsfAdPjSbj2RuObfm2XL83C5xVpoCSxXk0thnS7F9MdfwNBXkKNceZNA1yW_qCIvFP3bhfmopzyF14vSvv4yBkhx9k1RucjOHCVi0WquSh2ompkvd_IEHlMIjWHvAK0MycT-DfTWZXsEs5OjZMtbqdTiOMD3KSSwX6saImt9ejnPvFSpB0FW-Vi7xMXe-FiJ5rD5vIyKxi-zPYxDrs88zCXo9mIww==).
- Carbon management & abatement: GHG reduction programs, energy management, wet/thermal oxidizer scrubbers for air emissions at fabs. [Microchip corporate / reporting](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGilHBlI-Y57V1uFl3T_z06gy0d9dNRBtp8dnl-AjIK9NV-D4DNwI9MM0OMJGhNx60RjMm9ar4QuZeTQnVpO1oaDFSqbQbAKnL4guA_er5xnLqMFDs=) [PowerElectronicsNews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHH8SV6b3HIxQnRvLB7LlvOFzW4P05FMXmeS27vxMgVYyoglthoCDkmtn150pKUmSoLbHl9_bZyFI0k-ogLhr-IgGzyeyShIbSeTRZM5Z8aS76NjF3NsXw-vxC6MijogLZDMjE24LMY51b8Vo_qeJy6DIktE5cRGlYkm5hcKQUzwOuZTT7xRZl7V2zZf5ZXPDYGCL72H2k2gwZz4_w6ZJ-CxvOLkHdZjabh1o2PdBiIyhyAR5S3GWDs70eaA0hMMQ==).
- Water & waste: water recycling/reuse measures reported for fabs (general programmatic references); accelerated waste‑diversion program with elevated 2025/2030 diversion targets and a 2040 goal to divert 100% of waste from landfills. [PowerElectronicsNews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHYUDXOOw4234mW3jgKYyj8sEsaRZnEtPNnEKxEyuAzcl75DUn8fUF9NWGC4XR677qohWst2BhPj7FG0bH-42OINpYBTpIid94UbbNkwdplXQ-ZTM17NHEvBDsT9KLxn09obJj3MzyB_QCODbUpdoxOT0LouXHx9Xu2vtcQMWqMRgrMWEHH7kg81Vxxp2jifZqQwjpjUPd3YX_rYvvX6-JFVhg2B8CiYwF4Cm3Js89NW0VY9Ous02DzdH3OH37ZXA==) [CIE Online](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGwh9lRzDr8zoTiZqD55YMMgDlinLjO5wooh1sgRo7O7rbh1x9Wg_iPsU1mw-nWdKJ5CmjgLz7CrhmJjqx2QFA_VZr-tERvnWcHEHlKCSz3Ni2Rm9hkffo8NRwdiK61L2KwcSLQkPf0-haeOXgBntzl07S9QfmmbISNUoRjGU3lNPiqwfd8aOhS-p_Th29XL5PiHwMEe8iBbJZdGHVxa2mr3hX5mEEyXyWQUoSjCpfOKc6pY4VBYbCwBon7TwuwyhTD54g=).
- Supply‑chain standards: Responsible Business Alliance (RBA) membership and adoption of RBA Code of Conduct for supply‑chain labor/health/environment expectations. [Microchip RBA / corporate info](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHi1XRCRF8Tizd-XpGXiizbASz8wFm7I6VLw7F2a2E33Pz4iUVIiH9bR9XWufJvZlqQ-97zJCE0OUzXj5fOUc2nC2dWYr779Ulx7W6EBR8NJEGKQeFErwou8ZwVZTmnIJOTP36OdOjl3a4nzkQnlUP2uzRXzEWoqobz).

Why 17/25: Microchip has implemented a mix of credible sustainable technologies (renewables at facility level, product energy‑efficiency, waste diversion, water reuse, emissions controls). These are more than “basic” solutions, but they are not yet deployed at the same global scale or breadth as the largest industry leaders (who show much larger, multi‑100 MW PPA portfolios and higher renewables % across global operations).

Innovation Leadership — R&D, pilots and partnerships (18/25)
- Dedicated teams and programs: a “Sustainability Megatrend” team driving product and solution development for renewable energy generation, e‑mobility and sustainable infrastructure. [PowerElectronicsNews / Microchip pages](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG5e7JbJf1GtcKK1wMk57uJ8r3Xd7fzhk5rtnsfAdPjSbj2RuObfm2XL83C5xVpoCSxXk0thnS7F9MdfwNBXkKNceZNA1yW_qCIvFP3bhfmopzyF14vSvv4yBkhx9k1RucjOHCVi0WquSh2ompkvd_IEHlMIjWHvAK0MycT-DfTWZXsEs5OjZMtbqdTiOMD3KSSwX6saImt9ejnPvFSpB0FW-Vi7xMXe-FiJ5rD5vIyKxi-zPYxDrs88zCXo9mIww==) [Microchip sustainability pages](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGilHBlI-Y57V1uFl3T_z06gy0d9dNRBtp8dnl-AjIK9NV-D4DNwI9MM0OMJGhNx60RjMm9ar4QuZeTQnVpO1oaDFSqbQbAKnL4guA_er5xnLqMFDs=).
- Product innovation: mSiC (silicon carbide) power portfolio (MOSFETs, diodes, gate drivers) targeted at high‑voltage/high‑power, partnerships (example: Delta Electronics integration of mSiC into Delta power management systems); low‑power FPGA and SoC work aimed at doubling GOPS/watt for edge AI/compute, and reference demonstration designs (heat pump, polyphase meter). [Semiconductor‑Today / Morningstar coverage](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEPDWJiIgSfextiD2qB_SXJ3fcArHd6HRmrAq0C06eOYyWcsEqlGUV4FyhCnC6aaUyZltX1x-m-7LyUq7A9mdM_RONgG1XlFp2mth40Xk0cv_p-W1oNyKDAVtpkFJy-_TuTR97vpdl74Ba8OUBr0sIjtuQpJqrSBYTh-9ty8uEccM7t9PJQLpFnzuEH33TJ2A==) [Morningstar summary](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHHlSv2yHvq79DzQAwGVjhBcHpEm0Nat_zKxp0lxcEOl8Cosi3d9GaWVkw1Xpo8Hn99v0HkfgCkO8BkyjsqfdDU0n9wg-9lyEKYcI_BNTEK8NbbYESaYcC8xZAtA753iaD4V2kFWBkO4x5dwRYvKoLP9BWclR_QLGHxNNNqLa3dhaAN47S-qqSd_BLiFYcILQ19FVL5MBI_n-di0ADyFhL5u3kjYXIMAybvMP9CgeHItRtsWwUh4gnAL6mKTfFamRkO5ZB7ZXlcARGT1F7FvmgXS8lVdt-Wl8jz6WiHl-aVUtFCbo-2uTJNCd46WVk7aRG9IQicytQ=) [Microchip event materials](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEI0f2YkSRPbegrvKE4m2PYUIG3AD0PQzRgR2NAkUOKFsM9jEuqJSO8yo6DvdEwb5lXW8ukcO7QxW0_jkHS8aiKDa1alYLaHrve5zD2AeK-1KLCNVAzmOat1ubKYf-qsyyeHB79FflMW8VuSwBbKMsj55wx0sbkE1ZqOrBxI_uX2AuSvYrgB97hkAL4UWsrbZwJNqfvAg==).
- Academic & industry alliances: participation in multi‑party efforts (e.g., FUTUR‑IC microchip sustainability alliance / broader research collaborations such as Argonne‑linked initiatives on ultra‑efficient chips). These show engagement in precompetitive R&D on next‑gen low‑energy compute. [FUTUR‑IC / Argonne references](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG43pFS-BvZYcweyJaYqPBdmf3Tp-9LpnIMdN-Mb2w9h7WYw_iWFpDcH3ZRsZhVrLEuofoeCZkrEWmfulNKIv0ue9kusvQh4cdyGBGvA2lCcUFTvPhcBLUIQR9rALejssCtEyRL0lLIkANRLsS1L_TVou0Ct2xLmlQWW0lv_1yHQQKgOLq0577uiqXsay74HATOiJNCRwZJlsm8QbI97kC3-ZZNH6tsRTYIawXfspKn-eYbbHx104ON8g==) [Microchip coverage](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEI0f2YkSRPbegrvKE4m2PYUIG3AD0PQzRgR2NAkUOKFsM9jEuqJSO8yo6DvdEwb5lXW8ukcO7QxW0_jkHS8aiKDa1alYLaHrve5zD2AeK-1KLCNVAzmOat1ubKYf-qsyyeHB79FflMW8VuSwBbKMsj55wx0sbkE1ZqOrBxI_uX2AuSvYrgB97hkAL4UWsrbZwJNqfvAg==).
