Why 18/25: Microchip demonstrates strong targeted innovation (mSiC, low‑power architectures, system reference designs) and relevant partnerships. It is an active innovator in application‑level, energy‑efficient silicon and power electronics. It is not yet at the level of the largest integrated device manufacturers/foundries in terms of proprietary, industry‑leading sustainability patents and global program scale, but it is clearly above “moderate” innovation effort.

Measurable Impact — documented environmental/business outcomes (17/25)
- Emissions reductions: Microchip reports a 44% reduction in Scope 1 & 2 GHG emissions since 2018 and met a 2023 target of a 15% normalized reduction in Scope 1 emissions. The company has set a target to cut Scope 1 & 2 by 50% by 2030 and to reach net‑zero by 2040. [Microchip sustainability reporting / coverage](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGilHBlI-Y57V1uFl3T_z06gy0d9dNRBtp8dnl-AjIK9NV-D4DNwI9MM0OMJGhNx60RjMm9ar4QuZeTQnVpO1oaDFSqbQbAKnL4guA_er5xnLqMFDs=) [PowerElectronicsNews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHH8SV6b3HIxQnRvLB7LlvOFzW4P05FMXmeS27vxMgVYyoglthoCDkmtn150pKUmSoLbHl9_bZyFI0k-ogLhr-IgGzyeyShIbSeTRZM5Z8aS76NjF3NsXw-vxC6MijogLZDMjE24LMY51b8Vo_qeJy6DIktE5cRGlYkm5hcKQUzwOuZTT7xRZl7V2zZf5ZXPDYGCL72H2k2gwZz4_w6ZJ-CxvOLkHdZjabh1o2PdBiIyhyAR5S3GWDs70eaA0hMMQ==).
- Renewable project impact: the Thailand floating solar project (3.8 MW) is expected to meet ~16% of that facility’s electricity — a concrete site‑level contribution to renewables. [PowerElectronicsNews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGEZSFZVtnFnRva5iz-mdoHVnOTPpjW5zQc1vWkhmbkI-QJswGZeYZHhODfXAtLWUJ7RNP7Y6xKr-rTNWVbEueWA0CMMZWLFIhiBRNxw5WqoTsUppT4sfmx6Nqn1M91D5Qoy5GVWPKNzzSzuVzD8Z4nKqqEnJQx3-f5SftOKi8YfA865qylV9UlvAAGFr83GX0NXRvh4IjNVTWb6pvRt6gIjNILdkGqczHeoeKMuatLtL1BbXqBtfixV-rIFSXA) [PowerElectronicsNews summary](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHYUDXOOw4234mW3jgKYyj8sEsaRZnEtPNnEKxEyuAzcl75DUn8fUF9NWGC4XR677qohWst2BhPj7FG0bH-42OINpYBTpIid94UbbNkwdplXQ-ZTM17NHEvBDsT9KLxn09obJj3MzyB_QCODbUpdoxOT0LouXHx9Xu2vtcQMWqMRgrMWEHH7kg81Vxxp2jifZqQwjpjUPd3YX_rYvvX6-JFVhg2B8CiYwF4Cm3Js89NW0VY9Ous02DzdH3OH37ZXA==).
- Waste diversion: company reports that earlier targets were met ahead of schedule and that diversion targets have been raised for 2025/2030, with a 2040 goal for zero landfill. [PowerElectronicsNews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHYUDXOOw4234mW3jgKYyj8sEsaRZnEtPNnEKxEyuAzcl75DUn8fUF9NWGC4XR677qohWst2BhPj7FG0bH-42OINpYBTpIid94UbbNkwdplXQ-ZTM17NHEvBDsT9KLxn09obJj3MzyB_QCODbUpdoxOT0LouXHx9Xu2vtcQMWqMRgrMWEHH7kg81Vxxp2jifZqQwjpjUPd3YX_rYvvX6-JFVhg2B8CiYwF4Cm3Js89NW0VY9Ous02DzdH3OH37ZXA==) [YouTube/report summaries](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE0wttzYcmigKo2pjZ7E7sMUf_X4VqP3R5RzlYSIWOLdi50UktjxTJeCET__usLMo2zhEZCefiG7NSxA61g-z7VCK0mze6vmJn0xf6E8QRuVh-pJfh0MjqOzDsMNBQd_XwbpLhW3MQ=).
- Reporting/verification: Microchip publishes annual sustainability reports, uses GRI guidelines for reporting, and discloses to CDP; some fab sites hold ISO 14001 certifications (e.g., Gresham and Tempe noted). However, the record lacks public evidence (in the material we reviewed) that Microchip’s reduction targets are SBTi‑validated (unlike some peers). [Microchip reporting / CDP / ISO notes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGilHBlI-Y57V1uFl3T_z06gy0d9dNRBtp8dnl-AjIK9NV-D4DNwI9MM0OMJGhNx60RjMm9ar4QuZeTQnVpO1oaDFSqbQbAKnL4guA_er5xnLqMFDs=) [PowerElectronicsNews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHH8SV6b3HIxQnRvLB7LlvOFzW4P05FMXmeS27vxMgVYyoglthoCDkmtn150pKUmSoLbHl9_bZyFI0k-ogLhr-IgGzyeyShIbSeTRZM5Z8aS76NjF3NsXw-vxC6MijogLZDMjE24LMY51b8Vo_qeJy6DIktE5cRGlYkm5hcKQUzwOuZTT7xRZl7V2zZf5ZXPDYGCL72H2k2gwZz4_w6ZJ-CxvOLkHdZjabh1o2PdBiIyhyAR5S3GWDs70eaA0hMMQ==).

Why 17/25: Microchip has clear, documented, and measurable accomplishments (44% Scope 1/2 since 2018; 15% normalized reduction in 2023; site‑level solar delivering 16% of facility needs). Those are meaningful, but they stop short of “major” category thresholds used in this scoring rubric (>50% across measured metrics or company‑wide transformational figures) and there is limited public evidence (from available summaries) of comprehensive, externally validated SBTi targets or fully disclosed absolute year‑by‑year GHG tables for 2020–2024.

Future Strategy — commitments & roadmap (11/15)
- Explicit targets: Scope 1 & 2 reduction target 50% by 2030 and net‑zero by 2040; waste diversion to 100% by 2040. [PowerElectronicsNews / Microchip report](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHH8SV6b3HIxQnRvLB7LlvOFzW4P05FMXmeS27vxMgVYyoglthoCDkmtn150pKUmSoLbHl9_bZyFI0k-ogLhr-IgGzyeyShIbSeTRZM5Z8aS76NjF3NsXw-vxC6MijogLZDMjE24LMY51b8Vo_qeJy6DIktE5cRGlYkm5hcKQUzwOuZTT7xRZl7V2zZf5ZXPDYGCL72H2k2gwZz4_w6ZJ-CxvOLkHdZjabh1o2PdBiIyhyAR5S3GWDs70eaA0hMMQ==) [CIE Online coverage](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGwh9lRzDr8zoTiZqD55YMMgDlinLjO5wooh1sgRo7O7rbh1x9Wg_iPsU1mw-nWdKJ5CmjgLz7CrhmJjqx2QFA_VZr-tERvnWcHEHlKCSz3Ni2Rm9hkffo8NRwdiK61L2KwcSLQkPf0-haeOXgBntzl07S9QfmmbISNUoRjGU3lNPiqwfd8aOhS-p_Th29XL5PiHwMEe8iBbJZdGHVxa2mr3hX5mEEyXyWQUoSjCpfOKc6pY4VBYbCwBon7TwuwyhTD54g=).
- Programs & governance: Sustainability Megatrend team, Board Nominating/Governance & Sustainability Committee oversight; annual sustainability reporting and CDP disclosures. [Microchip reporting / governance](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGilHBlI-Y57V1uFl3T_z06gy0d9dNRBtp8dnl-AjIK9NV-D4DNwI9MM0OMJGhNx60RjMm9ar4QuZeTQnVpO1oaDFSqbQbAKnL4guA_er5xnLqMFDs=) [cloudfront governance note](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEUl3RjhF1hTUBYbukQgL73Y9faeVXfj6EDo8qu5RWcLMhAjIWaMLRrliKdT0IM6HjrChtQnzKmmxUO1P_UI8SfheR91xJHPJt-gh496Bi74gVQIBzZLkiFmqFihKv0bDLb2CyKHYc0jwMhHvFxaX6I62TnTpkehvw3chCZ0uestZ0gz0KQP_2BDciXrKRWKjRWUn_j1LMZ89y9xXkaaCKPrAsbuPrGubWLWFkhXSySepkNoT8K8qRRRAx1bndqF64z).
- Roadmap clarity: targets are specific and timed; however public disclosure on capital commitments, project pipeline (total MWs under contract), SBTi validation status or detailed Scope 3 reduction roadmaps is less complete in the materials reviewed. That reduces the score relative to companies that publish SBTi‑approved plans and large contracted renewable portfolios with published MW and MWh figures. [PowerElectronicsNews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG0ds119R2LP_qiG5ZOv_3M3jK00_SPdDQJENb_yvNXoHymy_2foV8OyP1S6BH9tVMLTy34t2IQXU-rxY-ycnH53c4hdUyQmDWj8-kWEcMOt34DCPbawsWX-OAeoBAlvSk_2C8z2VgZV1ohzmH-YrWEcxRm3oHRdBAZOMKyr84bzs_KyTk3BCkJmMMpKZ81aZO9WXLGZXhlnDLUU1tTorPGUN3E1OG42RhQXZhpEO5wQ0cZcucRPh4kQy9oaGNYSQ==) [manufacturingdigital](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHGPXXU3VAZyrTuOQ-Y1CvzE9y_PG0CNkoLBEglVsTh9LS3yTL82XitCLRcBlppqS2tscIT4iSsCPU9xeHIpuR2rNoRBtTo14_VcyfzIG_rUVZTMM_uijocCgJ0_9XDAFsxcViHE89iiOUZtwJdJq-B46h6dyKA1To3ZdePoZHWPHC0z9HuQO0uZyGLUi5WwrE_zPjA).

Why 11/15: Microchip has clear, time‑bound targets and governance structures (good), but some strategic items (SBTi validation, detailed capital commitments and extensive public portfolio data) are not clearly evidenced in the reviewed content.

Industry Position — how Microchip compares to peers (6/10)
- Relative position: Microchip is a credible, mid‑tier sustainability performer among semiconductor companies — active on renewables, energy‑efficient products, and reporting — but generally behind sector leaders on renewable procurement scale and SBTi validation. Large peers (Intel, TSMC, STMicroelectronics, Infineon) have reported higher renewables percentages, SBTi‑validated targets or more public absolute reductions and large PPAs / VPPA portfolios. [Benchmarking coverage / sector sources](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE9ZlkgAkR3-Ds9xAUTHpHGMFiQpjM2tWV6cHBbREPNfwz864Q0Hv3tX6lJVPW88LOtMX9Xp5EqzgA_12uA-K_B8jetuYUyIsbI8D-U-NGtDJPg1rXsvZsAuzRCDlS3cBm2pphyNtYSwh1WEb2P4NTtrlHV1mt44Wm1T_fSPwwHtyU_p7fiqRFUiHG0s8D-tuDEujo5ctOA) [manufacturingdigital / technologymagazine](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFAqRdNjKXZSQwCiot80JJvMZ4ct40fknSxmiHOQoWt5C7oXVpKfP-w1QoeYl6Pdw6tupWtshFj2XBNxy1F6so92rIZIzDm92nbKs4leL1LNF38842Cfjz7iJCTqsTDkEc1BC8tORk4U9oQKOj-mHZbKmHqlHhr92yZFT1APG35XHwkE35l-5_yhnDDyn9_32-p0ZXG5Ih3ReUTlpRUz83oLwiz) [ST/Infineon / Intel coverage](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEODVaTwA2ytHCnV-5YzZGOBf9NnwTaaXOk0YuqBrTXQWNkviTZHRJLP3m9BiFvxuWdD5TBpBtCE_wZXAWlXJSKqejWzcptiyUXmTdN2aCdcY7BGmPLP22Y3KzHgpMStTsee7_8Bb5FQepLOgopMnGbVPgrZB6grRCW-2nnZ02XdtbRelbOMcgwbb8e5cqgew==).
- Recognition: Microchip has received recognitions (e.g., Forbes Net Zero Leader 2024; Newsweek America’s Most Responsible Companies 2024), indicating positive external perception but not necessarily top‑tier scale leadership in sustainable technology adoption. [Microchip corporate / awards mention](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGilHBlI-Y57V1uFl3T_z06gy0d9dNRBtp8dnl-AjIK9NV-D4DNwI9MM0OMJGhNx60RjMm9ar4QuZeTQnVpO1oaDFSqbQbAKnL4guA_er5xnLqMFDs=).

Why 6/10: Microchip is above average relative to many smaller fabs/vendors, but below the very largest IDMs/foundries on the scale of renewables procurement and formally validated science‑based targets.

Score summary and calculation
- Technology Adoption: 17  
- Innovation Leadership: 18  
- Measurable Impact: 17  
- Future Strategy: 11  
- Industry Position: 6  
Total = 17 + 18 + 17 + 11 + 6 = 69/100

Concluding assessment (brief)
Microchip Technology is a solid mid‑tier performer on sustainable technology adoption and innovation. It has implemented concrete projects (notably the Thailand floating solar), demonstrable Scope 1/2 reductions, a focused sustainability product & R&D agenda (mSiC power devices, low‑power FPGAs, reference solutions for renewables and electrification), and clear medium‑term targets (50% Scope 1/2 by 2030; net‑zero 2040). The company’s main gaps versus top industry leaders are (1) scale and transparency of renewables procurement (large multi‑year PPAs/VPPA portfolios), (2) visible SBTi validation of targets in the materials reviewed, and (3) fully granular, easily accessible absolute annual emissions (Scope 1/2/3) datasets in the public domain. Overall: Microchip is moving in the right direction, demonstrating credible innovation and measurable wins, but is not yet a sector leader on the largest sustainability technology metrics. Score: 69/100.

